<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text"><i>Chrysothamnus viscidiflorus </i>has resinous foliage that burns readily. This fire-adapted species vigorously sprouts after fire, and its wind-dispersed seed readily colonizes areas after fire from off-site plants (Tirmenstein 1999i). Stands in northeastern California, Great Basin, and higher elevations of the Mojave Desert develop into stands of the <i>Artemisia tridentata, A. arbuscula, Purshia tridentata, </i>and <i>Pinus monophylla </i>alliances after 10 to 50 years.</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
