    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Modoc Plateau</b> (M261Ga, Gi, Gm). Stands occur in Lava Beds NM (DiPaolo et al. 2015).  Additionally, stands occur across the Modoc-Lassen mapping area (Boul et al. 2021b).</li>
        
            <li><b>Mono</b> (341De-f, Dh, Dj, Dl). Botanical records in area reflect possible stands (Consortium of California Herbaria 2019).</li>
        
            <li><b>Northwestern Basin and Range</b> (342Bc-e). Stands sampled in the Modoc-Lassen mapping project occur on recently disturbed sites (Boul et al. 2021b).</li>
        
            <li><b>Sierra Nevada</b> (M261Ec, Ei-k, En-o, Er, Eu). Botanical records in this region reflect possible stands (Consortium of California Herbaria 2019).</li>
        
            <li><b>Southeastern Great Basin</b> (341Fb-c, Ff). Stands occur on various landforms with disturbance from intermittent flooding, clearing, and fire (Thomas et al. 2004, Evens et al. 2014).</li>
        
            <li><b>Southern California Mountains and Valleys</b> (M262Bb). Botanical collections at Mt. Pinos indicate possible stands (Consortium of California Herbaria 2019).</li>
        
            <li><b>Southern Cascades</b> (M261Dh). Stands occur in Lava Beds NM at low to high elevations in early to mid-seral conditions including disturbance from fire and colonization in cheatgrass vegetation (DiPaolo et al. 2015).</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Management Considerations</h4>
	<div class="text"> As an early seral plant, <i>Chrysothamnus viscidiflorus </i>is well-suited to stabilize soil, control erosion, and revegetate disturbed sites. Plants have moderately deep roots and establish rapidly. Plants are an important browse for livestock and wildlife, though it is variable in palatability depending on subspecies (Tilley and St. John 2012, Tirmenstein 1999i). </div>
</div>

    

    

